source("R/setup.R")
# saved TaxaAgg_NA_red from MACROINV script
data = readRDS("data/taxa_an.rds")
# saved EnvAgg_NA_red2 from MACROINV script 
data2 = readRDS("data/taxa_env.rds")
# both object just before rda in line 334 
data %<>% mvabund()
data2 %<>% scale(scale = FALSE) %>% 
    as.data.frame()

Here I removed variables rather whimsically.

# correlations? 
corrplot::corrplot.mixed(corr = cor(data2), lower = "shade", upper = "number")

data3 = data2 %>% 
    dplyr::select(!c("O2", "FL"))
corrplot::corrplot.mixed(corr = cor(data3), lower = "shade", upper = "number")

# drop singeltons
data = data[,-which(colSums(data) == 1)]

Fit negative binomial model.

mod1= manyglm(data ~ ., data = data3)
walk(.x = 1:3, .f = ~ plot(mod1, which = .x))

# takes 27 seconds for 10 - 2700 for 1000, = 45 minutes
# 27 * 1200 = 32400 seconds = 540 minutes ~ 10 hours
mod1_res = anova.manyglm(mod1, 
         p.uni = "adjusted", 
         nBoot = 999,
         show.time = "all")
saveRDS(mod1_res, "data/many_nb.rds")
mod1_res$table %>% 
    kable(format = "html") %>% 
     kable_minimal %>% 
     kable_styling

# uni.p holds the univariate p-values. The first row is 
# the intercept which we do not care about. 
# uni.p is a matrix. To make our life easier for the 
# following steps we will convert it into a data frame
plot_data_species = data.frame(mod1_res$uni.p[-1,])
plot_data_species$variable = rownames(plot_data_species)
# Just to make the plot prettier we will replace all the 
# dots in variable and taxon names with spaces. 
names(plot_data_species) %<>% 
  str_replace_all(pattern = "\\.",
                  replacement = "\\ ")
# Here we pivot our data from the wide format (one column
# per taxon) to the long format (one columns which holds 
# the taxon and one which the p-value)
pivot_id   = which(names(plot_data_species) == "variable")
pivot_cols = names(plot_data_species)[-pivot_id]
plot_data_species %<>% pivot_longer(cols = pivot_cols)
                                    
plot_data_species$variable %<>% 
  str_replace_all(pattern = "\\.",
                  replacement = "\\ ")
plot_data_species %>% 
        ggplot(aes(x = value, y = name)) + 
        geom_point(aes(col = variable)) + 
        geom_vline(xintercept = 0.05) + 
  theme(text = element_text(size = 10))
a        = quantile(abs(coef(mod1)), .75)
colort   = colorRampPalette(c("blue", "white", "red"))

variable_names = rownames(mod1$stderr.coefficients)

mod1$stderr.coefficients %>% 
    as.data.frame() %>% 
    mutate(variable = variable_names) %>% 
    pivot_longer(cols = !(variable)) -> 
    SE
mod1$coefficients%>% 
    as.data.frame() %>% 
    mutate(variable = variable_names) %>% 
    pivot_longer(cols = !(variable), values_to = "estimate", 
                 names_to = "taxa") -> 
    CO
CO$SE = SE$value
CO %<>% 
    mutate(lb = estimate - 2*SE, 
           ub = estimate + 2*SE)
CO %<>% 
    mutate(significant_lb = sign(estimate) == sign(lb), 
           significant_ub = sign(estimate) == sign(ub),
           significant = significant_lb & significant_ub)

# If not significant set estimate to zero 
CO %<>% mutate(
    estimate = ifelse(significant, estimate, 0)
)

# convert back ot wide format 
CO %>% 
    dplyr::select(!c("SE", "lb","ub","significant_lb" ,"significant_ub", "significant")) %>% 
    pivot_wider(id_cols = variable, 
                names_from = taxa,
                values_from = estimate) %>% 
    as.data.frame() -> 
    coef_plot 
rownames(coef_plot) = coef_plot$variable
coef_plot %<>% filter(variable != "(Intercept)")
coef_plot %<>% dplyr::select(-variable)
col_id = which(colSums(coef_plot) == 0)
coef_plot = coef_plot[,-col_id]
row_id = which(rowSums(coef_plot) == 0)
coef_plot = coef_plot[-row_id,]
any (colSums(coef_plot) == 0)
## [1] FALSE
#a        = quantile(abs(as.matrix(coef_plot)), .75)
plot.tas = levelplot(
  t(as.matrix(coef_plot)),
  ylab = "",
  xlab  = "",
  col.regions = colort(100),
  at = seq(-1, 1, length = 100),
  scales = list(x = list(rot = 45))
)
print(plot.tas)
